            9 => [
                'text' => 'As shown in Figure 1, there is a box that generates two (2) numerical values B1 and B2 when two (2) positive integers A1 and A2 are entered. B1 has the same value as A2, and B2 is the remainder of A1 divided by A2. As shown in Figure 2, when two (2) boxes are connected, and 49 is entered as A1 and 11 is entered as A2 in the left box, what is the value of B2 generated from the right box?',
                'image' => '
                    Figure 1:
                        A1 ──┐
                             ├── [Box] ── B1 (= A2)
                        A2 ──┘
                             └── B2 (remainder of A1 ÷ A2)
                    
                    Figure 2:
                        49 ──┐     B1=11 ──┐
                             ├── [Box] ──┼──┐
                        11 ──┘     B2=5 ──┘  │
                                              ├── [Box] ── B2 = ?
                                              │
                         (from left box B1) ──┘
                    
                    First box: 49 ÷ 11 = 4 remainder 5, so B1=11, B2=5
                    Second box: A1=11 (from B1 of first box), A2=5 (from B2 of first box)
                    11 ÷ 5 = 2 remainder 1, so B2=1
