            54 => [
                'text' => 'In a development project for a system, there is a plan to create 36 programs with the same size. It was first planned to assign only Mr. A who can create six (6) programs per week, but the plan was changed and it was decided to assign two (2) people: Mr. A, and Mr. B who has half the productivity of Mr. A. When the cost per week for Mr. A and Mr. B is 300 thousand yen and 200 thousand yen respectively, how much is the change in the cost as compared to the original plan? Here, Mr. A and Mr. B perform activities in parallel, and the efficiency of Mr. A and Mr. B are always fixed.',
                'image' => '
                    Original plan:
                    - Mr. A only: 6 programs/week
                    - Total programs: 36 → 36/6 = 6 weeks
                    - Cost: 6 weeks × 300,000 yen = 1,800,000 yen
                    
                    New plan:
                    - Mr. A: 6 programs/week, Mr. B: 3 programs/week (half of Mr. A)
                    - Combined: 9 programs/week
                    - Time: 36/9 = 4 weeks
                    - Cost: (4 × 300,000) + (4 × 200,000) = 1,200,000 + 800,000 = 2,000,000 yen
                    
                    Change: 2,000,000 - 1,800,000 = +200,000 yen increase
                ',
                'choices' => [
                    'a' => 'A decrease of 800 thousand yen',
                    'b' => 'A decrease of 300 thousand yen',
                    'c' => 'An increase of 200 thousand yen',
                    'd' => 'An increase of 1,200 thousand yen'
                ]
