            71 => [
                'text' => 'When the purchase and sales of a product in April are as in the table below, what is the inventory value in yen for the product at the end of April according to the moving average method? The moving average method calculates the average unit price of products in the inventory each time a purchase is made, and uses the average unit price for products in the inventory immediately beforehand for the calculation of the inventory value.',
                'image' => '
                    Table:
                    +--------+----------------+----------+-----------+-------+-----------+-------+---------------+-------+
                    | Date   | Note           | Replenishment          | Shipping               | Inventory                      |
                    |        |                | Quantity| Unit price| Total | Quantity | Total   | Average price| Total |
                    +--------+----------------+---------+-----------+-------+----------+---------+--------------+-------+
                    | Apr 1  | Carry over     | 100     | 10        | 1,000 |          |         | 10           | 1,000 |
                    | Apr 8  | Purchase       | 100     | 14        | 1,400 |          |         | 12           | 2,400 |
                    | Apr 18 | Sales          |         |           |       | 150      |         |              |       |
                    | Apr 29 | Purchase       | 50      | 16        | 800   |          |         |              |       |
                    +--------+----------------+---------+-----------+-------+----------+---------+--------------+-------+
                    
                    After Apr 8: 200 units at avg price 12 = 2,400
                    Apr 18: Sold 150 units at avg price 12 = 1,800
                    Remaining: 50 units at avg price 12 = 600
                    Apr 29: Purchase 50 units at 16 = 800
                    New inventory: 100 units, total value 600 + 800 = 1,400
                    Average price = 1,400 / 100 = 14
                    End of April inventory value = 1,400 yen
                ',
                'choices' => [
                    'a' => '1,280',
                    'b' => '1,300',
                    'c' => '1,400',
