        33 => [
            'explanation' => 'In email: To and CC recipients can see each other\'s addresses. BCC recipients are hidden from To/CC recipients but can see To/CC addresses. Mr. Q (CC) can see Mr. P (To) but not Mr. R (BCC).',
            'steps' => [
                'Step 1: Understand email addressing:',
                '   - To: Primary recipients (visible to all)',
                '   - CC: Carbon Copy (visible to all)',
                '   - BCC: Blind Carbon Copy (hidden from To/CC)',
                'Step 2: Apply to scenario:',
                '   - Mr. P (To): sees Mr. Q, not Mr. R',
                '   - Mr. Q (CC): sees Mr. P, not Mr. R',
                '   - Mr. R (BCC): sees Mr. P and Mr. Q',
                'Step 3: Evaluate options:',
                '   - a: False (P and Q cannot see R)',
                '   - b: False (P can see Q in CC)',
                '   - c: True (Q can see P in To) ✓',
